#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 3. Tatiyavagga → kosalavaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn3.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Kosala "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Puggalasutta "
msgstr "21. Persons "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.210, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.21:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.21:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi of Kosala went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.21:1.3"
msgid "“cattārome, mahārāja puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Great king, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "sn3.21:1.4"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "sn3.21:1.5"
msgid "Tamotamaparāyano, tamojotiparāyano, jotitamaparāyano, jotijotiparāyano. "
msgstr "~The dark bound for darkness, ~the dark bound for light, ~the light bound for darkness, and ~the light bound for light. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.94, pts2ed1.211, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.21:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahārāja puggalo tamotamaparāyano hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a person dark and bound for darkness? "

#. VAR: venakule → veṇakule (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.21:2.2"
msgid "Idha, mahārāja, ekacco puggalo nīce kule paccājāto hoti, caṇḍālakule vā venakule vā nesādakule vā rathakārakule vā pukkusakule vā dalidde appannapānabhojane kasiravuttike, yattha kasirena ghāsacchādo labbhati. "
msgstr "It’s when some person is reborn in a low family—a family of outcastes, bamboo-workers, hunters, chariot-makers, or waste-collectors—poor, with little to eat or drink, where life is tough, and food and shelter are hard to find. "

#. VAR: bavhābādho → bahvābādho (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.21:2.3"
msgid "So ca hoti dubbaṇṇo duddasiko okoṭimako bavhābādho kāṇo vā kuṇī vā khañjo vā pakkhahato vā, na lābhī annassa pānassa vatthassa yānassa mālāgandhavilepanassa seyyāvasathapadīpeyyassa. "
msgstr "And they’re ugly, unsightly, deformed, chronically ill—one-eyed, crippled, lame, or half-paralyzed. They don’t get to have food, drink, clothes, and vehicles; garlands, perfumes, and makeup; or bed, house, and lighting. "

msgctxt "sn3.21:2.4"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr "And they do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn3.21:2.5"
msgid "So kāyena duccaritaṃ caritvā vācāya duccaritaṃ caritvā manasā duccaritaṃ caritvā, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

# NOTE: This seems to be the only occurence of the term lohitamala
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn3.21:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso andhakārā vā andhakāraṃ gaccheyya, tamā vā tamaṃ gaccheyya, lohitamalā vā lohitamalaṃ gaccheyya. "
msgstr "This person is like someone who goes from darkness to darkness, from blackness to blackness, from bloodstain to bloodstain. "

msgctxt "sn3.21:3.2"
msgid "Tathūpamāhaṃ, mahārāja, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.21:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahārāja, puggalo tamotamaparāyano hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is dark and bound for darkness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
