msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

# NOTE: The last phrase doesn’t mirror the positive version of the simile. BB has “enters an underground darkness”; maybe, but the text doesn’t say underground; and anyway, wouldn’t that be to “descend” once more?
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn3.21:7.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, puriso pāsādā vā hatthikkhandhaṃ oroheyya, hatthikkhandhā vā assapiṭṭhiṃ oroheyya, assapiṭṭhiyā vā pallaṅkaṃ oroheyya, pallaṅkā vā pathaviṃ oroheyya, pathaviyā vā andhakāraṃ paviseyya. "
msgstr "This person is like someone who descends from a stilt longhouse to an elephant; from an elephant to horseback; from horseback to a couch; and from a couch to the ground; and from the ground they enter darkness. "

msgctxt "sn3.21:7.2"
msgid "Tathūpamāhaṃ, mahārāja, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.21:7.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahārāja, puggalo jotitamaparāyano hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is light and bound for darkness. "

